# {{context|grammar|lang=en}} A pronoun in the possessive case.

====Usage notes====
Being pronouns, possessive pronouns can only appear on their own, standing in for a noun or similar noun-like word. Words like {{m|en|my}} or {{m|en|their}}, which modify nouns and cannot stand on their own, are also commonly referred to as "possessive pronouns", because of their relationship to the [[personal pronoun]]s. These are more correctly called {{m|en|possessive determiner|possessive determiners}} or {{m|en|possessive adjective|possessive adjectives}}, however, as they are not pronouns in the strict sense.

